I’ve often been asked the question, “how do you feel about faux plants?”. The answer is simple, not everyone has the light or the care level to have living plants in their space. So I’d rather you bring in a faux plant than force a living plant into a space where it will suffer and eventually die.  Faux plants can elevate spots in your home where you never thought you’d be able to have greenery before. With all of the faux plants in the Hilton Carter for Target collection, my goal was to make them look as real as possible so that they could really bring that lush, calm feeling. Here are a few tips on where and how to style them! 🌿🙏🏾💚

node.text: Over the holidays I partnered with @stgermaindrinks to develop some WILD ideas for entertaining during holiday season. To pull off these themed moments, I teamed up with the talented @sashabikoff and @madamebleu_stgermain. Inspired by the interactive nature of the Parisian salons in the 1920s, we chose three art movements from that time (Art Deco, Cubism and Surrealism) to take our holiday gatherings to the next level. Here are the highlights from the Surrealist nightcap moment and how it all came together! If you missed the Art Deco or Cubism moments, you can find them here in my IGTV. Enjoy! #StGermainPartner #SalonStGermain

node.text: 6 years ago today I convinced my next door neighbor to go on a date with me. We didn’t have much in common. I was a filmmaker and she was a dentist. What would we talk about? We had zero friends in common. Who would bridge the gap? We didn’t listen to the same music. She was more Robyn while I was more 21 Savage. What would we dance to? All of these uncertainties created an immense amount of excitement. As we sat there during that dinner jumping from topic to topic, it was her laughter and ability to be her true self out the gate that sold me. It felt like a mutual, “take all of me or take nothing” sort of attitude was in the air that night. As I walked her to her front door, kissed her good night and then walked 20 feet to the next door that was mine, I thought, “I’m in a whole lot of trouble now.” But honestly she was. I tricked her into marrying me and then followed that up with helping me make a little version of her. 👼🏽😉 While we might not have matched up well on paper, in reality, our connection was magnetic. ❤️ #mylove

node.text: When designing the remodel of our home, one of the goals was to make sure that from wherever you stood on the first floor, that you’d have the ability to look out of a window and see greenery. And not just from one position. From any spot, if you turned your head 180 degrees, you’d be able to see out of a minimum of 3 windows. The reason this was important is because our home is surrounded by many evergreen trees, so the windows allow for that blurring of indoor/outdoor. So in some cases, I’ve limited the amount of indoor plants in rooms so that the outdoor plants can make an impression. 🌿

node.text: Now for the glow up! We’ve finally finished the exterior renovations on our home! We purchased this older home because we loved the silhouette and it’s charm. While there were many things that needed to be updated about it, many we tried our very best to keep original. The one thing we did change through the entire exterior of the house were the windows. We loved the original windows but many of them were broken or inoperable. We went with the black framed @andersen_windows because they would give the facade that modern touch while not going too far. We did add an extra window on the staircase to allow more light to pour into our foyer and of course to sprinkle a little greenery where there couldn’t be before. We had the stucco power washed, painted and patched. We painted it Greek Villa by SW and painted the gable end and shutters Basil by SW. Basil was a warmer green than the  original green, and I felt it would bring more life to the facade, instead of making it feel dark and lonely. The last thing we updated was the landscaping. This was mainly due to our water line bursting weeks into purchasing the home. Btw, if you buy a home, get the insurance that covers the water line. Because we didn’t 🤦🏾‍♂️ One side of our yard had to be completely dug up to repair the problem. So all new sod went down and I’ve added a few new topiaries in that hopefully over the next few years will grow in and start to take real shape. I guess I’ll get to get my Edward Scissorhands on! And speaking of plants, you’ll see that many of our tropical plants are taking in the good life by getting that Baltimore humidity and taking in all of that bright indirect light, from this north facing direction. What a “welcome” mat! With Fall right around the corner, all of these plants will make their way indoors come mid October. That will make our home an indoor oasis come winter. I’m down for that! Overall, we are fortunate to call this place home. Fortunate to have been able to put in the work that was required to make it ours. Fortunate to have a place to raise our daughter in and host our family and friends in. Swipe L to see what the house looked like when we first purchased it.🖤🌿🏡

And just like that…we are forever changed. 🙏🏾 Meet the new member of our family, HOLLAND HEIDI CARTER! I’ve never been so scared and so filled with intense love as I watched my beautiful, strong wife push out this little creation. And then Holland emerged and my heart exploded into a million pieces, only to fuse back together again, this time much larger and more delicate. I mean, I’m crying writing this right now. Here was an instant game changer. An instant life changer. And without a doubt, a future heartbreaker. While I spent her first few days staring at her for hours, making promise after promise to her, I did quietly explain to her that I’m flawed. Not every decision I make will be the right one. Not every word that will form from my mouth will be my bond. But here I am, her’s, her mother’s…until I’m in the dirt. And after that, sit in the shade of the tree that grows from me. 

Friends, if you see me smiling, it’s this face I’m thinking about. If you see me crying, it’s this face I’m thinking about. Tears of joy. How lucky am I?! I found true love, twice! HOW LUCKY AM I?!!!! ❤️🙏🏾👼🏽🤱🏻#thankful #girldad #love
